      "heading_path": [
        "Technical data"
      ],
      "text": "For technical data not owned by Public Services and Procurement Canada (PSPC), you must ensure that the government obtains rights for its distribution and use.",
      "order": 1,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "block_id": "block_0002",
      "block_type": "paragraph",
      "heading": "Technical data",
      "heading_path": [
        "Technical data"
      ],
      "text": "If the necessary technical data is available through normal business channels, such as Canadian Standards Association (CSA) specifications or standards, businesses are responsible for obtaining it themselves.",
      "order": 2,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "block_id": "block_0003",
      "block_type": "paragraph",
      "heading": "Technical data",
      "heading_path": [
        "Technical data"
      ],
      "text": "If technical data needs to be sent to businesses from an alternate source, such as the client, the solicitation must not be posted until this data is available from that source. The solicitation must clearly identify how to obtain the data.",
